q# Emacs Hotkeys Cheatsheet

This file provides a quick reference for the custom keybindings in this configuration.

## Global & Core
| Key | Command | Description |
|-----|---------|-------------|
| `C-g` | `ntgo/keyboard-quit-dwim` | Region-aware keyboard quit |
| `C-x k` | `kill-current-buffer` | Kill the active buffer immediately |
| `<f3>` | `flymake-goto-next-error` | Jump to next Flymake error/warning |
| `<f5>` | `project-compile` | Run compilation for the current project |
| `S-<f5>` | `project-recompile` | Re-run the last compilation |
| `S-<arrow>` | `windmove-*` | Move focus between windows |

## Navigation & Search (Consult & Embark)
| Key | Command | Description |
|-----|---------|-------------|
| `C-x b` | `consult-buffer` | Enhanced buffer/bookmark switcher |
| `M-l` | `consult-git-grep` | Ripgrep across the git repository |
| `M-s` | `consult-line` | Fuzzy search lines in current buffer |
| `M-y` | `consult-yank-pop` | Browse and insert from kill ring |
| `C-.` | `embark-act` | Run context-sensitive actions |
| `C-;` | `embark-dwim` | "Do What I Mean" action on target |
| `C-h B` | `embark-bindings` | List all available keybindings |

